spec: asyncio_extra109
version: ">=3.9"
backend: python_module(asyncio)

docs: https://docs.python.org/3/library/asyncio-stream.html

provenance:
  derived_from:
    - "https://docs.python.org/3/library/asyncio-stream.html — Python asyncio streams documentation"
    - "Test vectors verified with Python 3.14.3 on macOS/Darwin 25.4.0, 2026-04-10"
  not_derived_from:
    - "CPython source: Lib/asyncio/streams.py"
  notes:
    - "This spec extends asyncio_extra108.zspec.zsdl."
    - "This spec covers: wave 254 theme — asyncio.StreamReader and asyncio.StreamWriter class identity (__name__, __module__, __bases__[0].__name__, __mro__.__len__), and asyncio.streams module classes. NEW in extra109: asyncio.StreamReader.__name__=='StreamReader', __module__=='asyncio.streams', __bases__[0].__name__=='object', __mro__.__len__()==2; asyncio.StreamWriter.__name__=='StreamWriter', __module__=='asyncio.streams', __bases__[0].__name__=='object', __mro__.__len__()==2; type(asyncio.StreamReader.read).__name__=='function'; StreamReader.read.__qualname__=='StreamReader.read' (len=17, co_argcount=2: self, n); StreamReader.readline.__qualname__=='StreamReader.readline' (len=21, co_argcount=1: self only); type(asyncio.StreamWriter.write).__name__=='function'; StreamWriter.write.__qualname__=='StreamWriter.write' (len=18, co_argcount=2: self, data); StreamWriter.drain.__qualname__=='StreamWriter.drain' (len=18, co_argcount=1: self only); asyncio.open_connection.__code__.co_name=='open_connection' (co_argcount=2); asyncio.start_server.__code__.co_name=='start_server' (co_argcount=3). All verified with Python 3.14.3 on macOS/Darwin 25.4.0, 2026-04-10."
    - "asyncio.StreamReader.__bases__[0].__name__ == 'object'. StreamReader inherits directly from object with MRO [StreamReader, object] (length=2). StreamReader is the class for reading data from async streams; read() takes self and n (co_argcount=2); readline() takes only self (co_argcount=1). Verified with Python 3.14.3 on macOS/Darwin 25.4.0, 2026-04-10."
    - "asyncio.StreamWriter.__bases__[0].__name__ == 'object'. StreamWriter inherits directly from object with MRO [StreamWriter, object] (length=2). write() takes self and data (co_argcount=2); drain() takes only self (co_argcount=1). Verified with Python 3.14.3 on macOS/Darwin 25.4.0, 2026-04-10."
    - "asyncio.open_connection.__code__.co_argcount == 2 (host and port as positional args; other params are keyword-only). asyncio.start_server.__code__.co_argcount == 3 (client_connected_cb, host, port as positional args). Both are coroutine functions in asyncio.streams. open_connection.__qualname__.__len__()==15; start_server.__qualname__.__len__()==12. Verified with Python 3.14.3 on macOS/Darwin 25.4.0, 2026-04-10."
    - "All expected values verified with Python 3.14.3 on macOS/Darwin 25.4.0, 2026-04-10."
  created_at: "2026-04-10T00:00:00Z"

error_model: python_exceptions

# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# asyncio.StreamReader class identity — extra109
#
# Wave 254 theme: StreamReader and StreamWriter class identity.
#
# asyncio.StreamReader.__name__               == 'StreamReader'       (mro len=2, base=object)
# asyncio.StreamReader.__module__             == 'asyncio.streams'
# asyncio.StreamReader.__bases__[0].__name__  == 'object'
# asyncio.StreamReader.__mro__.__len__()      == 2
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------

