  description: "asyncio.StreamReader class identity checks in asynciostream109 namespace — wave 254 theme: asyncio.StreamReader.__name__.__eq__('StreamReader')==True (len=12); asyncio.StreamReader.__module__.__eq__('asyncio.streams')==True; asyncio.StreamReader.__bases__[0].__name__.__eq__('object')==True (StreamReader inherits directly from object, MRO=[StreamReader, object], length=2); asyncio.StreamReader.__mro__.__len__()==2; asyncio.StreamReader.__qualname__.__eq__('StreamReader')==True (len=12); type(asyncio.StreamReader.read).__name__.__eq__('function')==True (Python-defined); StreamReader.read.__qualname__.__eq__('StreamReader.read')==True (len=17: 'StreamReader.'=13+'read'=4=17); StreamReader.read.__code__.co_argcount==2 (self and n); type(asyncio.StreamReader.readline).__name__.__eq__('function')==True (Python-defined); StreamReader.readline.__qualname__.__eq__('StreamReader.readline')==True (len=21: 'StreamReader.'=13+'readline'=8=21); StreamReader.readline.__code__.co_argcount==1 (self only); compare read co_argcount=2 vs readline co_argcount=1; read qualname=17 < readline=21; verified with Python 3.14.3"
